r_n=\\frac{z_{n+2}}{z_n}$ and $s_n=\\frac{z_{n+1}}{z_n}$. Then we have $\\{r_n\\}_{n=1}^\\infty$ and $\\{s_n\\}_{n=1}^\\infty$ with the following properties:\n\n\n\nWrite $z_n=x_n+iy_n$ where $x_n$ and $y_n$ are real. Then:\n  $$\\begin{cases}\\dfrac{r_{n+1}}{r_n}=\\dfrac{x_{n+1}^2-y_{n+1}^2+x_{n+1}x_n-y_{n+1}y_n+2i(x_ny_{n+1}+x_{n+1}y_n)}{x_n^2-y_n^2+x_nx_{n+1}-y_ny_{n+1}+2i(y_nx_{n+1}-x_ny_{n+1})}\\\\=\\dfrac{(x_{n+1}^2-y_{n+1}^2+x_{n+1}x_n-y_{n+1}y_n)^2+(x_ny_{n+1}+x_{n+1}y_n)^2}{(x_n^2-y_n^2+x_nx_{n+1}-y_ny_{n+1})^2+(y_nx_{n+1}-x_ny_{n+1})^2}\\\\\\left(\\dfrac{x_{n+1}^2-y_{n+1}^2+x_{n+1}x_n-y_{n+1}y_n}{x_n^2-y_n^2+x_nx_{n+1}-y_ny_{n+1}}\\right)^2-1\\\\+2i\\left(\\dfrac{x_ny_{n+1}+x_{n+1}y_n}{x_n^2-y_n^2+x_nx_{n+1}-y_ny_{n+1}}\\right)^2\\sin(2\\Theta)\\end{cases}$$ Where $\\cot(\\Theta)=\\frac{x_{n+1}+y_{n+1}}{x_n+y_n}$ when $x_n+y_n>0$ and $\\cot(\\Theta)=\\frac{x_{n+1}-y_{n+1}}{x_n-y_n}$ when $x_n-y_n>0$.\n$\\dfrac{z_{n+1}^2}{z_nz_{n+2}}=\\dfrac{x_{n+1}^2+y_{n+1}^2}{x_nx_{n+2}+y_ny_{n+2}}=1$. Therefore $r_{n+1}=r_n^3$.$\\bf(\\text{induction})$.\n$\\{\\Re(r_m)\\}_{m=0,1,\\cdots}$ is strictly increasing.\n$\\{\\Im(r_m)\\}_{m=0,1,\\cdots}$ is strictly decreasing.\n\n\nThe proof of Problem 187 in topological vector spaces, J\u6210\u5c31in 2005 is similar to that above.\n$\\{s_n\\}_{n=1}^\\infty$ with the following properties:\n\n$\\dfrac{r_n}{s_n}=\\frac{x_{n+2}}{x_{n+1}^2+y_{n+1}^2}$ (induction)\n$s_{n+3}=\\frac{x_n}{x_n+y_n}\\cdot s_{n+1}$\n\n$\\lim_{n\\to\\infty}\\Re(s_n)+\\Im(s_n)=2\\iff \\begin{cases}\\lim_{n\\to\\infty}\\dfrac{x_n}{2+x_n}=-\\cos\\frac{\\pi}8\\\\\\lim_{n\\to\\infty}\\dfrac{y_n}{2+x_n}=2\\sin\\frac{\\pi}8 \\iff \\dfrac{x_n}{2+x_n}+\\dfrac{y_n}{2+x_n}=2\\sin\\frac{\\pi}8^2+\\cos\\frac{\\pi}8^2=1\\end{cases} \\iff \\boxed{\\Re(s_n)+\\Im(s_n)=1}$\n</answer>", "truth": "65536", "reward_format": 0.0, "reward_answer": 0.0, "reward_total": 0.0}, {"prompt": "A conversation between User and Assistant. The User asks a question, and the Assistant solves i